#compdef cm3
# =============================================================================
# cm3 — Critical Mass Modula-3 Compiler — the canonical
#        actively-maintained MODULA-3 compiler.  Originally
#        developed at Critical Mass Software (a Modula-3
#        consultancy founded by Bill Kalsow + Eric Muller in
#        the late 1990s after they left DEC SRC), now
#        community-maintained at modula3/cm3.  Distinguishing:
#          - Compiles to NATIVE CODE via multiple backends:
#            integrated assembler (M3 BACKEND), gcc-derived
#            M3CC backend, or LLVM backend
#          - INTEGRATED BUILD SYSTEM via the "QUAKE" build-
#            description language (a Tcl-influenced DSL embedded
#            in cm3) — m3makefile / m3overrides drive builds
#          - SIX BUILD MODES via mode flags: -build, -clean,
#            -ship, -find, -depend, -realclean
#          - GROUP-WRITABLE BUILD OUTPUTS via -gw flag for
#            shared dev environments
#          - PARALLEL BACKEND via -pb for multi-core compiles
#          - PACKAGE-BASED build organization (M3-LIBS + M3-SYS
#            + M3-DEPS conventional source tree layout)
#          - SELF-HOSTED — cm3 is written in Modula-3
#        Used as the canonical OSS Modula-3 implementation
#        + supported alongside Polytechnique Montréal's PM3
#        (an alternative Modula-3 compiler).
#
# Author:  Critical Mass Software (Bill Kalsow + Eric Muller,
#          ex-DEC SRC engineers who worked on Modula-3 from
#          its inception 1986-1995) → modula3 GitHub community
#          (after Critical Mass dissolved, the cm3 source was
#          open-sourced + community-maintained).  Modula-3
#          language designed by: Luca Cardelli (Olivetti, later
#          Microsoft Research), Jim Donahue (Olivetti), Lucille
#          Glassman (DEC SRC), Mick Jordan (DEC SRC), Bill
#          Kalsow (DEC SRC), Greg Nelson (DEC SRC) — published
#          "Modula-3 Report" 1988-1992.
# Source:  https://github.com/modula3/cm3
#          https://github.com/modula3/cm3/blob/master/m3-sys/cm3/src/Main.m3
#          https://github.com/modula3/cm3/blob/master/m3-sys/cm3/src/Makefile.m3
# CLI:     m3-sys/cm3/src/Makefile.m3 — Modula-3 source for
#          cm3 (self-hosted!).  Argv processed via Modula-3's
#          standard library `Arg.Pop()` (the Arg interface
#          provides argv stack-pop semantics).  Hand-rolled
#          CASE statement on first character of each option
#          dispatches to per-letter Text.Equal checks.
# Library: Modula-3 stdlib Arg interface + CASE-on-character
#          (Modula-3 has no formal "argv parsing library" — the
#           stdlib `Arg` interface provides STACK-BASED argv
#           access: `Arg.Pop()` pops the next argument from a
#           shared stack of remaining args.  cm3's ConvertOption
#           uses `Text.GetChar(arg, 1)` to dispatch on first
#           character after the leading dash, then `Text.Equal`
#           for full-name matching within each letter group.)
